{
  "text": "The free state \u0393 \u2206 depends on \u2206 only through its 1-matrix \u03b3 \u2206 . One can see how by comparing [CITATION_1] or (18) to [CITATION_2] . Suppose \u2206 \u2208 D and let \u03b3 \u2206 be as in [CITATION_3] , so that \u2206 has natural modes g i and natural occupation numbers n i . The natural modes f i of \u0393 \u2206 must be the same as the natural modes g i of \u2206. Using the g i as the reference modes for the Fock basis |n : n \u2208 F or |n : n \u2208 B , the free density operator \u0393 \u2206 is described by formula (13) or (14), wherein the parameters are related to the n i by p i = n i in the fermion case and",
